title.narrative: OTP 5 - SOCIAL PROTECTION

description.narrative: By 2022, the social protection system and mechanisms have the capacity to reach the most deprived families with children, are able to deliver equitable services and financial assistance., which contributes to Access To Inclusive Social Protection, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Reducing Child Poverty, Social Protection. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Partnerships And Engagement: Public And Private, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022, Moldova national systems and services are more inclusive, able to protect the rights of children, and respond to the needs of the most vulnerable in an equitable way

description.narrative: In 2021, despite a challenging COVID-19 situation and the absence of a constituted Government in the first half of the year, UNICEF Moldova conducted repeated analysis on the socio-economic impact of the pandemic and continued to collaborate with the Ministry of Finance, development partners and others to strengthen the dialogue around macro-level policies and strategies that guide national sectoral policies and secure adequate financing for, and quality of child related services. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:11/01/2022
